---
// site/src/components/Boundaries.astro
//
// PORT-04 / D-10: four boundaries, each framed constraint -> deliberate
// decision. Always single-column, full-width at every breakpoint -- a grid
// would visually trivialize content D-10 wants read one at a time
// (23-UI-SPEC.md "Responsive Behavior").
//
// Positioned immediately before the closing CTA (D-05) so a visitor reads
// "this bot is offline unless the owner is running it" before clicking
// Add-to-Discord, not after.
//
// Copy is verbatim from 23-UI-SPEC.md's Copywriting Contract, cross-checked
// against `.planning/PROJECT.md` §Key Decisions line by line (Phase 21 rows).
// No drift found: `/ask` staying global-but-self-scoped, the four purged
// tables (config/queues/jams/scoped memories), and `guild_blocklist` surviving
// purges all match the shipped-reality ledger exactly -- boundary 4's copy is
// used as-is, not adjusted.
//
// Voice: deliberately NOT sarcastic anywhere in this section (CLAUDE.md
// Critical Rule 6 / D-09) -- this is serious content, read it back straight.
import BoundaryItem from "./BoundaryItem.astro";

const boundaries = [
  {
    label: "verification wall",
    bodyHtml:
      "discord requires verification and privileged-intent approval past 100 servers — a process this project hasn't pursued. the target scale is modest (single-digit to low-dozens of servers), so verification was scoped out rather than pursued for a portfolio deployment.",
    showOfflineDot: false,
  },
  {
    label: "on-demand hosting",
    bodyHtml:
      "dexter runs on the owner's residential pc, not an always-on host — the free-tier cloud options that exist all get blocked by youtube's datacenter-ip rules. hosting stays on-demand rather than forcing a workaround. <strong>the bot is offline unless the owner is currently running it</strong> — invite it, and don't expect it online 24/7 yet.",
    showOfflineDot: true,
  },
  {
    label: "full-savage + kill-switch",
    bodyHtml:
      "dexter's sarcasm runs at full intensity in every server — there's no per-guild tone dial. rather than build a settings surface for something core to the bot's identity, the owner gets a real, fast kill-switch instead: list every server dexter is in, silence one instantly, or force it to leave and blacklist a re-invite — two enforced choke points, not a scattered set of per-command checks.",
    showOfflineDot: false,
  },
  {
    label: "hybrid memory scoping",
    bodyHtml:
      "dexter remembers things about users via a vector-search long-term memory store. <code>/roast @user</code>, ambient roasts, and proactive callbacks only recall memories scoped to the current server — a third party's history never crosses servers. <code>/ask</code> stays global, but only for your own memory (self-recall, no cross-user exposure is possible). when dexter leaves a server, that server's data — config, queues, jams, and its scoped memories — is purged.",
    showOfflineDot: false,
  },
];
---

<section id="boundaries" class="section section--secondary" aria-labelledby="boundaries-heading">
  <div class="section-inner">
    <h2 id="boundaries-heading" class="boundaries-heading">known limits</h2>
    <p class="boundaries-subhead">four deliberate tradeoffs, disclosed here instead of discovered later.</p>
    <div class="boundary-list">
      {
        boundaries.map((b) => (
          <BoundaryItem label={b.label} bodyHtml={b.bodyHtml} showOfflineDot={b.showOfflineDot} />
        ))
      }
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  /* Deliberately plain: no ">" accent glyph on this heading (unlike Demo,
     Features, CTA) -- this section is visually distinct from the amber
     "action" sections precisely because it is not a feature (23-UI-SPEC.md
     "Copywriting Contract"). */
  .boundaries-heading {
    margin: 0;
  }

  .boundaries-subhead {
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-size: var(--text-body-size);
    line-height: var(--text-body-line-height);
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    margin: var(--space-sm) 0 0 0;
    max-width: 640px;
  }

  .boundary-list {
    margin-top: var(--space-xl);
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-md);
  }
</style>
